      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, so you're saying the background itself is a reason to sentence them differently? I'm trying to understand the logic here. If they committed the exact same crime, why does the environment they grew up in change the \"correct\" sentencing approach? Doesn't that mean we are essentially punishing Defendant B more for his socioeconomic status rather than the crime itself?",
